==Description==

The '''Std ClarifySelection''' command displays a list of nearby geometrical entities of different kinds next to the cursor when hovering over ther model.

==Usage==

# Place the coursor over the geometry in the [[3D_View|3D View]].
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Clarify Selection}} option from the context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|G}} then {{KEY|G}}.
# A list with several geometrical object types will appear next to the cursor. Depending on what objects are located near the cursor, it may include:
#* Objects
#* Faces
#* Edges
#* Vertices
#* Other
# Choose the object type and then pick the specific object from the list. Objects are highlighted and partial transparency is enabled when hovering over the items on the list.
# The picked object will become selected.

